  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response in Somaliland</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Somaliland is slowly emerging out of a period of severe extended drought, mainly due to two consecutive seasons of failed rains, particularly in the eastern regions. However, the impact of the drought has affected all sectors including health and production. Forced displacement is one of the defining humanitarian and development challenges as far as the impact of the drought is concerned and many host communities are already battling against acute shortages of supplies including life-saving materials.

To ensure the children have the potential to achieve normal growth, early identification and reversal of growth faltering will be essential to enabling optimal child development and health through PlumpyDoz. World Concern will distribute 30 tons of PlumpyDoz for a period of 6 months to children in 15 &#x2013; 20 villages in the Sool and Sanaag Regions. World Concern will target children under five years of age who are severely malnourished, especially those in stabilization centers, supporting allowances for health workers involved in mobile services, strengthening the capacity of selected health facilities to deliver emergency services and improving access to essential medical drugs.</narrative>
  </description>
